{{version030}}
{{flavour|The Crypt is a huge repository for the ancient dead. The air is chill and fetid, the walls cold and damp. Bones are strewn liberally everywhere and every noise echoes worryingly, violating the overbearing silence of the grave.

This branch is unusually silent: sounds travel farther here.

The entrance to this branch can be found between levels 2 and 3 of the Vaults.

This branch is 3 levels deep.

This branch contains the entrance to the Tomb.
}}
{{flavour|These stairs lead to an ancient crypt. Unfortunately, not everything that was buried there had the decency to stay dead.}}

[[File:Crypt entry.png]] '''The Crypt''' is a 3-floor [[branch]], found between [[the Vaults]]:2 and 3. It is filled with all manner of [[undead]] opponents, and although it does not contain a [[rune of Zot]], it does hold the [[list of mummies|mummy]]-guarded entrance to [[the Tomb]], as well as a significant amount of treasure guarded by powerful undead foes on the final floor.

==Layout==
The Crypt is made up of claustrophobic, winding hallways and large open chambers, all of which are built of [[wand of digging|undiggable]] stone or metal [[wall]]s.

The Crypt is also a [[Noise#Ambient noise|very silent place]], so noise carries farther than usual. Most residents are dead quiet, but even the noise made by your weapons will attract attention.

===Crypt:3===
The third floor of the Crypt always has a treasure [[vault]], which can be sized anywhere from a modest room to all of the map. These always contain some of the most powerful undead enemies in the game, but often hold living and [[list of constructs#Golems|golem]] opponents as well. 

Some of the treasure vault loot will be Necromancy themed loot, such as [[draining]], [[vampiric]], or [[pain]]-[[brand]]ed weapons, [[ring of positive energy|rings of positive energy]], the [[Necronomicon]], [[staff of death|staves of death]], or one of several similarly themed [[unrand]]s.

==Strategy==
Crypt is almost entirely filled with undead creatures, so [[holy wrath]] and [[Dispel Undead]] are more useful here. Likewise, [[negative energy]] and [[torment]] are common, so bring rN+.

The following monsters deserve special attention:
*{{monsterlink|Ancient champion}} - These foes can fire [[Iron Shot]]s and have decent damage. When [[haste]]d, they can deal good damage against any character.
*{{monsterlink|Bone dragon}} - A high damage, highly durable undead enemy. Simple, but threatening.
*{{monsterlink|Curse skull}} - These fast-moving and high [[AC]] skulls can [[torment]] you and [[Summon Undead]].
*{{monsterlink|Ancient lich}} & {{monsterlink|Dread lich}} - top-tier spellcasters. Ancient liches deal massive damage with their spells, dread liches can paralyse you or summon dangerous demons.
*{{monsterlink|Phantasmal warrior}} - not terribly dangerous on their own, but they halve your [[willpower]], making you vulnerable to being hexed by [[vampire knight]]s, liches, or other enemies.

===Useful Traits===
*A [[holy wrath]] weapon
*[[Dispel Undead]]
*Strong physical defenses
*[[Negative energy]] resistance
*[[See invisible]]
<!--
==Crypt:3 vaults==
'''Eye to Eye With the Devil''': A small chamber which forces you to deal with multiple [[ancient lich]]es, [[curse skull]]s, and other potent threats before reaching the loot.

'''Haunted Forest''': A full-floor graveyard, filled with dead [[tree]]s, gravestones, and mausoleums, each of which contains a variety of angry inhabitants.

'''Cryptofortress''': A full-floor undead fortress, guarded by [[iron golem]]s. Exploration will reveal powerful liches, mummies, and vampires guarding the various loot heaps.

'''Church of pain''': A cross-shaped map with 4 different monster sets: skeletons, vampires, ghosts, and mummies.

'''Quadcrypt''': A full-floor vault divided in four quadrants: burial hoard (NE), chapel of [[Kikubaaqudgha]] (NW), catacombs (SE), and crematory (SW).

'''Elkab''': A triparte Egyptian temple. Like the church of pain, it has four sets of monsters: skeleton, ghost, vampire, and mummy.

'''The death's head''': A full-floor skull-shaped vault.

'''Unholy cathedral''': A very compact vault with altars to [[Yredelemnul]] and [[Kikubaaqudgha]].
-->
